
User & Group Manipulation
useradd 
  -g <group name or number>
  -G <group name(s) or number(s)>
  -m create home directory if one doesn't exist
  -u <UID> user ID (UID) or number, default is the next available #
usermod
  -g <group name or number>
  -G <group name(s) or number(s)>
  -u <UID> user ID (UID) or number, default is the next available #
userdel







